  "text": "Adenovirus-mediated Gene Transfer in H4IIEC3 Hepatocytes-Cells were transfected with adenoviruses as described previously [CITATION_1] . Briefly, H4IIEC3 hepatocytes were grown to 90% confluence in 24-well multiplates and transfected with adenoviruses encoding dominant negative (DN) ␣1 and ␣2 AMPK, constitutive active (CA) AMPK, or LacZ for 4 h. The cells were incubated with DMEM for 24 h after removing the adenoviruses; total RNA was then extracted.",
